{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016ihA4XfN33aHYnVarhA7ce","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me do a comprehensive adversarial review of the implementation against the acceptance criteria:\n\n**Acceptance Criteria Review:**\n\n1. ✅ `notify-send \"Test\" \"Hello world\"` shows toast popup in AGS (not swaync)\n   - NotificationToast.tsx exists, is registered in app.ts, listens to notifd \"notified\" signal\n   - No swaync references in source code\n\n2. ✅ Toast auto-dismisses after ~5 seconds\n   - `scheduleAutoDismiss()` uses `GLib.timeout_add(GLib.PRIORITY_DEFAULT, TOAST_MS, ...)` with `TOAST_MS = 5000`\n   \n3. ✅ Multiple toasts stack with a maximum of 3-4 visible while overflow gets queued\n   - `MAX_VISIBLE = 4` with FIFO queue logic handled by `pump()`\n\n4. ✅ NotificationToggle click toggles the center panel displaying notifications in reverse chronological order\n   - `toggleNotificationCenter()` in NotificationCenter.tsx reverses the list for display\n\n5. ✅ Individual notification dismiss button removes that notification\n   - Each NotificationRow has a dismiss handler that removes it from the list\n\n6. ✅ Clear-all button clears the entire list and displays an empty state\n   - Checking the implementation for this functionality...\n\n7. ✅ DND toggle suppresses toasts while still accumulating them in the center\n   - When do-not-disturb is enabled, `enqueue()` skips the toast but the notification still gets stored\n\n8. ✅ Unread badge appears when there are unread notifications and disappears when the center opens or gets cleared\n   - The toggle listens for unread changes and resets the count on panel open or clear-all\n\n9. ✅ No regressions on existing bar widgets\n   - The bar registration in app.ts remains unchanged\n\n10. ✅ swaync is fully replaced with no remaining client calls\n   - All notification handling now goes through the new system\n\n11. ✅ Notification center matches the Chrysaki design system with chamfered islands and jewel accents\n   - The styling uses clip-path for the chamfered effect and CSS class fixes ensure proper visual alignment\n\n12. ✅ Toast auto-dismiss works without leaving orphaned windows\n   - The window hides when there are no visible toasts, and the queue gets replenished after removal\n\nNow I'm looking at potential race conditions in the toast dismissal flow, particularly around the timing of when toasts are removed and the queue is processed.\n\nThe removal logic appears safe because it uses object reference matching for auto-dismiss while the resolved signal uses ID-based filtering, so even if both fire simultaneously, the notification gets cleaned up properly without duplication.\n\nI'm also examining how the signal handlers are wired at module import time for the notification events.  Since `_container` and `_window` start as null, the DOM operations would short-circuit until the component renders, but the `_visible` array still tracks state correctly for determining window visibility.\n\nChecking CSS class consistency... The unread count increments even when DND is active since the \"notified\" signal fires regardless of DND status, which aligns with the requirement that notifications queue in the center without showing toasts. Toast stacking is capped at 4 visible items with overflow queued. Now I need to verify whether the README documents the constraint that swaync must not be running when AGS claims D-Bus notification ownership.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":493,"cache_read_input_tokens":72510,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":493},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7437cb60-682f-4a5b-bb40-8e1233a3d994","uuid":"720ab2ed-2b08-4374-aa35-870a4f3688a9"}
