{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014dctqRJchPuXQV3sPsfo23","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Chrysaki\n     2→\n     3→![Version](https://img.shields.io/badge/version-1.1.0-20969c?style=flat-square&labelColor=252836&logo=semanticrelease&logoColor=20969c)\n     4→![Ports](https://img.shields.io/badge/ports-16-1a8a6a?style=flat-square&labelColor=252836&logo=github&logoColor=1a8a6a)\n     5→![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-FBB13C?style=flat-square&labelColor=252836&logo=opensourceinitiative&logoColor=FBB13C)\n     6→\n     7→A dark-first, jewel-toned design system and theme suite. Hard geometric corners, tri-primary accent palette, and perceptually-uniform OKLCH colour engineering.\n     8→\n     9→Ports for 16 applications across terminal, editor, desktop, and web categories — inspired by the porting methodology of Rosé Pine. A consistent palette-first approach where every application maps the same named colour tokens to its own theming API.\n    10→\n    11→---\n    12→\n    13→## Palette\n    14→\n    15→### Surfaces\n    16→\n    17→| Token | Hex | Swatch | Use |\n    18→|:------|:----|:-------|:----|\n    19→| Abyss | `#0f1117` | ![](https://via.placeholder.com/15/0f1117/0f1117?text=+) | Deepest background, modal backdrops |\n    20→| Base | `#161821` | ![](https://via.placeholder.com/15/161821/161821?text=+) | Primary canvas |\n    21→| Surface | `#1c1f2b` | ![](https://via.placeholder.com/15/1c1f2b/1c1f2b?text=+) | Cards, sidebars |\n    22→| Raised | `#252836` | ![](https://via.placeholder.com/15/252836/252836?text=+) | Hover states, popups |\n    23→| Elevated | `#2e3142` | ![](https://via.placeholder.com/15/2e3142/2e3142?text=+) | Tooltips, floating elements |\n    24→| Border | `#363a4f` | ![](https://via.placeholder.com/15/363a4f/363a4f?text=+) | Dividers, input borders |\n    25→\n    26→### Primary Accents (Tri-Primary)\n    27→\n    28→| Token | Base | Light | Dim | Domain |\n    29→|:------|:-----|:------|:----|:-------|\n    30→| Emerald | `#14664e` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/14664e/14664e?text=+) | `#1a8a6a` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/1a8a6a/1a8a6a?text=+) | `#0e4a38` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/0e4a38/0e4a38?text=+) | Growth, creation, links |\n    31→| Royal Blue | `#122858` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/122858/122858?text=+) | `#1c3d7a` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/1c3d7a/1c3d7a?text=+) | `#0c1a40` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/0c1a40/0c1a40?text=+) | Structure, navigation, depth |\n    32→| Amethyst | `#3a2068` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/3a2068/3a2068?text=+) | `#583090` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/583090/583090?text=+) | `#1e1040` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/1e1040/1e1040?text=+) | Creativity, identity, focus |\n    33→\n    34→### Secondary Accents\n    35→\n    36→| Token | Base | Light | Dim | Domain |\n    37→|:------|:-----|:------|:----|:-------|\n    38→| Teal | `#197278` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/197278/197278?text=+) | `#20969c` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/20969c/20969c?text=+) | `#0f4f54` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/0f4f54/0f4f54?text=+) | Transitional, metadata, tags |\n    39→| Blonde | `#FBB13C` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/FBB13C/FBB13C?text=+) | `#FCC96A` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/FCC96A/FCC96A?text=+) | `#C4861C` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/C4861C/C4861C?text=+) | Emphasis, numbers, highlights |\n    40→| Error | `#8C2F39` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/8C2F39/8C2F39?text=+) | `#b53f4a` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/b53f4a/b53f4a?text=+) | `#5e1f25` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/5e1f25/5e1f25?text=+) | Errors, danger |\n    41→\n    42→### Text\n    43→\n    44→| Level | Hex | Swatch |\n    45→|:------|:----|:-------|\n    46→| Primary | `#e0e2ea` | ![](https://via.placeholder.com/15/e0e2ea/e0e2ea?text=+) |\n    47→| Secondary | `#a0a4b8` | ![](https://via.placeholder.com/15/a0a4b8/a0a4b8?text=+) |\n    48→| Muted | `#6a6e82` | ![](https://via.placeholder.com/15/6a6e82/6a6e82?text=+) |\n    49→| Inverse | `#0f1117` | ![](https://via.placeholder.com/15/0f1117/0f1117?text=+) |\n    50→\n    51→---\n    52→\n    53→## Design Rules\n    54→\n    55→- **Zero border-radius** throughout. Geometric alternatives: chamfer (`clip-path` 8px cuts), hexagonal (tags/badges), trapezoid (active tab indicators).\n    56→- **Royal Blue and Amethyst are fill colours only** — too dark for text on dark surfaces.\n    57→- **Safe text accents on dark**: Emerald Lt, Teal, Teal Lt, Blonde, Blonde Lt, Error.\n    58→- **Gradient direction**: Emerald always leads (leftmost / topmost).\n    59→- **Background hierarchy**: Editor is Base (`#161821`, lightest). Chrome (tab bar, activity bar) is Abyss (`#0f1117`, darkest). Everything in between uses Surface → Raised → Elevated.\n    60→\n    61→---\n    62→\n    63→## Ports\n    64→\n    65→### Terminal Emulators and Shell\n    66→\n    67→| App | Config Format | File |\n    68→|:----|:-------------|:-----|\n    69→| Alacritty | TOML | [`alacritty/chrysaki.toml`](alacritty/chrysaki.toml) |\n    70→| Kitty | INI conf | [`kitty/theme.conf`](kitty/theme.conf) |\n    71→| Windows Terminal | JSON scheme | [`windows-terminal/chrysaki.json`](windows-terminal/chrysaki.json) |\n    72→| tmux | `.tmux.conf` | [`tmux/chrysaki.conf`](tmux/chrysaki.conf) |\n    73→| PowerShell | PSReadLine `.ps1` | [`powershell/chrysaki-psreadline.ps1`](powershell/chrysaki-psreadline.ps1) |\n    74→\n    75→### Editors and Developer Tools\n    76→\n    77→| App | Config Format | File |\n    78→|:----|:-------------|:-----|\n    79→| Neovim | Lua colorscheme | [`nvim/chrysaki.lua`](nvim/chrysaki.lua) |\n    80→| VS Code | JSON theme | [`vscode/chrysaki-color-theme.json`](vscode/chrysaki-color-theme.json) |\n    81→| Gitui | RON theme | [`gitui/theme.ron`](gitui/theme.ron) |\n    82→\n    83→### Desktop and System\n    84→\n    85→| App | Config Format | File |\n    86→|:----|:-------------|:-----|\n    87→| GTK 3/4 | CSS + settings.ini | [`gtk/gtk.css`](gtk/gtk.css), [`gtk/settings.ini`](gtk/settings.ini) |\n    88→| Steam / SteamOS | CSS injection | [`steam/libraryroot.custom.css`](steam/libraryroot.custom.css) |\n    89→| Discord | Vencord/BetterDiscord CSS | [`discord/Chrysaki.theme.css`](discord/Chrysaki.theme.css) |\n    90→| Spotify | Spicetify color.ini + CSS | [`spicetify/color.ini`](spicetify/color.ini), [`spicetify/user.css`](spicetify/user.css) |\n    91→\n    92→### Web and Documentation\n    93→\n    94→| App | Config Format | File |\n    95→|:----|:-------------|:-----|\n    96→| Firefox | userChrome + userContent | [`firefox/userChrome.css`](firefox/userChrome.css), [`firefox/userContent.css`](firefox/userContent.css) |\n    97→| Marp | CSS theme | [`marp/chrysaki.css`](marp/chrysaki.css) |\n    98→\n    99→---\n   100→\n   101→## Installation\n   102→\n   103→### VS Code\n   104→\n   105→Copy the `vscode/` folder to `~/.vscode/extensions/chrysaki-theme-1.0.0/`, then select **Chrysaki** via `Ctrl+K Ctrl+T`.\n   106→\n   107→### Windows Terminal\n   108→\n   109→Add the contents of `windows-terminal/chrysaki.json` to the `\"schemes\": [...]` array in your `settings.json`, then set `\"colorScheme\": \"Chrysaki\"` in your profile defaults.\n   110→\n   111→### PowerShell\n   112→\n   113→Dot-source the script in your `$PROFILE`:\n   114→```powershell\n   115→. \"path\\to\\chrysaki-psreadline.ps1\"\n   116→```\n   117→\n   118→### Kitty\n   119→\n   120→Save `kitty/theme.conf` to `~/.config/kitty/theme.conf`, then add to `kitty.conf`:\n   121→```conf\n   122→include theme.conf\n   123→```\n   124→\n   125→### tmux\n   126→\n   127→Append `tmux/chrysaki.conf` to `~/.tmux.conf`, or source it:\n   128→```bash\n   129→source-file ~/.tmux/chrysaki.conf\n   130→```\n   131→\n   132→### Neovim\n   133→\n   134→Copy `nvim/chrysaki.lua` to `~/.config/nvim/colors/chrysaki.lua`, then:\n   135→```lua\n   136→vim.cmd(\"colorscheme chrysaki\")\n   137→```\n   138→\n   139→### Gitui\n   140→\n   141→Copy `gitui/theme.ron` to `~/.config/gitui/theme.ron`. Gitui loads it automatically.\n   142→\n   143→### GTK\n   144→\n   145→```bash\n   146→mkdir -p ~/.config/gtk-3.0 ~/.config/gtk-4.0\n   147→cp gtk/gtk.css ~/.config/gtk-3.0/gtk.css\n   148→cp gtk/gtk.css ~/.config/gtk-4.0/gtk.css\n   149→cp gtk/settings.ini ~/.config/gtk-3.0/settings.ini\n   150→```\n   151→\n   152→Log out and back in for changes to take effect.\n   153→\n   154→### Steam / SteamOS\n   155→\n   156→Copy `steam/libraryroot.custom.css` to the Steam UI directory:\n   157→- Linux/SteamOS: `~/.steam/steam/steamui/libraryroot.custom.css`\n   158→- Windows: `C:/Program Files (x86)/Steam/steamui/libraryroot.custom.css`\n   159→\n   160→Restart Steam.\n   161→\n   162→### Firefox\n   163→\n   164→1. Enable `toolkit.legacyUserProfileCustomizations.stylesheets` in `about:config`\n   165→2. Copy `firefox/userChrome.css` and `firefox/userContent.css` to `<profile>/chrome/`\n   166→3. Restart Firefox\n   167→\n   168→### Discord (Vencord)\n   169→\n   170→Copy `discord/Chrysaki.theme.css` to `~/.config/Vencord/themes/` and enable in Vencord settings.\n   171→\n   172→### Spotify (Spicetify)\n   173→\n   174→```bash\n   175→mkdir -p ~/.config/spicetify/Themes/Chrysaki\n   176→cp spicetify/* ~/.config/spicetify/Themes/Chrysaki/\n   177→spicetify config current_theme Chrysaki\n   178→spicetify config color_scheme Base\n   179→spicetify apply\n   180→```\n   181→\n   182→### Marp\n   183→\n   184→```bash\n   185→marp --theme marp/chrysaki.css input.md\n   186→```\n   187→\n   188→Or in VS Code with the Marp extension, add to `.vscode/settings.json`:\n   189→```json\n   190→{\n   191→    \"markdown.marp.themes\": [\"./marp/chrysaki.css\"]\n   192→}\n   193→```\n   194→\n   195→---\n   196→\n   197→## CSS Custom Properties\n   198→\n   199→Drop these into any CSS project to use Chrysaki tokens:\n   200→\n   201→```css\n   202→--chrysaki-abyss:        #0f1117;\n   203→--chrysaki-base:         #161821;\n   204→--chrysaki-surface:      #1c1f2b;\n   205→--chrysaki-raised:       #252836;\n   206→--chrysaki-elevated:     #2e3142;\n   207→--chrysaki-border:       #363a4f;\n   208→--chrysaki-emerald:      #14664e;\n   209→--chrysaki-emerald-lt:   #1a8a6a;\n   210→--chrysaki-emerald-dim:  #0e4a38;\n   211→--chrysaki-blue:         #122858;\n   212→--chrysaki-blue-lt:      #1c3d7a;\n   213→--chrysaki-blue-dim:     #0c1a40;\n   214→--chrysaki-amethyst:     #3a2068;\n   215→--chrysaki-amethyst-lt:  #583090;\n   216→--chrysaki-amethyst-dim: #1e1040;\n   217→--chrysaki-teal:         #197278;\n   218→--chrysaki-teal-lt:      #20969c;\n   219→--chrysaki-teal-dim:     #0f4f54;\n   220→--chrysaki-blonde:       #FBB13C;\n   221→--chrysaki-blonde-lt:    #FCC96A;\n   222→--chrysaki-blonde-dim:   #C4861C;\n   223→--chrysaki-error:        #8C2F39;\n   224→--chrysaki-error-lt:     #b53f4a;\n   225→--chrysaki-error-dim:    #5e1f25;\n   226→--chrysaki-text:         #e0e2ea;\n   227→--chrysaki-text-sec:     #a0a4b8;\n   228→--chrysaki-text-muted:   #6a6e82;\n   229→--chrysaki-text-inverse: #0f1117;\n   230→```\n   231→\n   232→---\n   233→\n   234→*Part of the [obKidian](https://github.com/Kiriketsuki/obKidian) vault system.*\n   235→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7437cb60-682f-4a5b-bb40-8e1233a3d994","uuid":"60c9eda0-1f56-45b6-b56a-5d09ed349d0a","timestamp":"2026-03-17T12:02:36.384Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/kiriketsuki/dots/chrysaki-ralph-ags-notification-center/README.md","content":"# Chrysaki\n\n![Version](https://img.shields.io/badge/version-1.1.0-20969c?style=flat-square&labelColor=252836&logo=semanticrelease&logoColor=20969c)\n![Ports](https://img.shields.io/badge/ports-16-1a8a6a?style=flat-square&labelColor=252836&logo=github&logoColor=1a8a6a)\n![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-FBB13C?style=flat-square&labelColor=252836&logo=opensourceinitiative&logoColor=FBB13C)\n\nA dark-first, jewel-toned design system and theme suite. Hard geometric corners, tri-primary accent palette, and perceptually-uniform OKLCH colour engineering.\n\nPorts for 16 applications across terminal, editor, desktop, and web categories — inspired by the porting methodology of Rosé Pine. A consistent palette-first approach where every application maps the same named colour tokens to its own theming API.\n\n---\n\n## Palette\n\n### Surfaces\n\n| Token | Hex | Swatch | Use |\n|:------|:----|:-------|:----|\n| Abyss | `#0f1117` | ![](https://via.placeholder.com/15/0f1117/0f1117?text=+) | Deepest background, modal backdrops |\n| Base | `#161821` | ![](https://via.placeholder.com/15/161821/161821?text=+) | Primary canvas |\n| Surface | `#1c1f2b` | ![](https://via.placeholder.com/15/1c1f2b/1c1f2b?text=+) | Cards, sidebars |\n| Raised | `#252836` | ![](https://via.placeholder.com/15/252836/252836?text=+) | Hover states, popups |\n| Elevated | `#2e3142` | ![](https://via.placeholder.com/15/2e3142/2e3142?text=+) | Tooltips, floating elements |\n| Border | `#363a4f` | ![](https://via.placeholder.com/15/363a4f/363a4f?text=+) | Dividers, input borders |\n\n### Primary Accents (Tri-Primary)\n\n| Token | Base | Light | Dim | Domain |\n|:------|:-----|:------|:----|:-------|\n| Emerald | `#14664e` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/14664e/14664e?text=+) | `#1a8a6a` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/1a8a6a/1a8a6a?text=+) | `#0e4a38` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/0e4a38/0e4a38?text=+) | Growth, creation, links |\n| Royal Blue | `#122858` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/122858/122858?text=+) | `#1c3d7a` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/1c3d7a/1c3d7a?text=+) | `#0c1a40` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/0c1a40/0c1a40?text=+) | Structure, navigation, depth |\n| Amethyst | `#3a2068` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/3a2068/3a2068?text=+) | `#583090` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/583090/583090?text=+) | `#1e1040` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/1e1040/1e1040?text=+) | Creativity, identity, focus |\n\n### Secondary Accents\n\n| Token | Base | Light | Dim | Domain |\n|:------|:-----|:------|:----|:-------|\n| Teal | `#197278` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/197278/197278?text=+) | `#20969c` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/20969c/20969c?text=+) | `#0f4f54` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/0f4f54/0f4f54?text=+) | Transitional, metadata, tags |\n| Blonde | `#FBB13C` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/FBB13C/FBB13C?text=+) | `#FCC96A` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/FCC96A/FCC96A?text=+) | `#C4861C` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/C4861C/C4861C?text=+) | Emphasis, numbers, highlights |\n| Error | `#8C2F39` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/8C2F39/8C2F39?text=+) | `#b53f4a` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/b53f4a/b53f4a?text=+) | `#5e1f25` ![](https://via.placeholder.com/10/5e1f25/5e1f25?text=+) | Errors, danger |\n\n### Text\n\n| Level | Hex | Swatch |\n|:------|:----|:-------|\n| Primary | `#e0e2ea` | ![](https://via.placeholder.com/15/e0e2ea/e0e2ea?text=+) |\n| Secondary | `#a0a4b8` | ![](https://via.placeholder.com/15/a0a4b8/a0a4b8?text=+) |\n| Muted | `#6a6e82` | ![](https://via.placeholder.com/15/6a6e82/6a6e82?text=+) |\n| Inverse | `#0f1117` | ![](https://via.placeholder.com/15/0f1117/0f1117?text=+) |\n\n---\n\n## Design Rules\n\n- **Zero border-radius** throughout. Geometric alternatives: chamfer (`clip-path` 8px cuts), hexagonal (tags/badges), trapezoid (active tab indicators).\n- **Royal Blue and Amethyst are fill colours only** — too dark for text on dark surfaces.\n- **Safe text accents on dark**: Emerald Lt, Teal, Teal Lt, Blonde, Blonde Lt, Error.\n- **Gradient direction**: Emerald always leads (leftmost / topmost).\n- **Background hierarchy**: Editor is Base (`#161821`, lightest). Chrome (tab bar, activity bar) is Abyss (`#0f1117`, darkest). Everything in between uses Surface → Raised → Elevated.\n\n---\n\n## Ports\n\n### Terminal Emulators and Shell\n\n| App | Config Format | File |\n|:----|:-------------|:-----|\n| Alacritty | TOML | [`alacritty/chrysaki.toml`](alacritty/chrysaki.toml) |\n| Kitty | INI conf | [`kitty/theme.conf`](kitty/theme.conf) |\n| Windows Terminal | JSON scheme | [`windows-terminal/chrysaki.json`](windows-terminal/chrysaki.json) |\n| tmux | `.tmux.conf` | [`tmux/chrysaki.conf`](tmux/chrysaki.conf) |\n| PowerShell | PSReadLine `.ps1` | [`powershell/chrysaki-psreadline.ps1`](powershell/chrysaki-psreadline.ps1) |\n\n### Editors and Developer Tools\n\n| App | Config Format | File |\n|:----|:-------------|:-----|\n| Neovim | Lua colorscheme | [`nvim/chrysaki.lua`](nvim/chrysaki.lua) |\n| VS Code | JSON theme | [`vscode/chrysaki-color-theme.json`](vscode/chrysaki-color-theme.json) |\n| Gitui | RON theme | [`gitui/theme.ron`](gitui/theme.ron) |\n\n### Desktop and System\n\n| App | Config Format | File |\n|:----|:-------------|:-----|\n| GTK 3/4 | CSS + settings.ini | [`gtk/gtk.css`](gtk/gtk.css), [`gtk/settings.ini`](gtk/settings.ini) |\n| Steam / SteamOS | CSS injection | [`steam/libraryroot.custom.css`](steam/libraryroot.custom.css) |\n| Discord | Vencord/BetterDiscord CSS | [`discord/Chrysaki.theme.css`](discord/Chrysaki.theme.css) |\n| Spotify | Spicetify color.ini + CSS | [`spicetify/color.ini`](spicetify/color.ini), [`spicetify/user.css`](spicetify/user.css) |\n\n### Web and Documentation\n\n| App | Config Format | File |\n|:----|:-------------|:-----|\n| Firefox | userChrome + userContent | [`firefox/userChrome.css`](firefox/userChrome.css), [`firefox/userContent.css`](firefox/userContent.css) |\n| Marp | CSS theme | [`marp/chrysaki.css`](marp/chrysaki.css) |\n\n---\n\n## Installation\n\n### VS Code\n\nCopy the `vscode/` folder to `~/.vscode/extensions/chrysaki-theme-1.0.0/`, then select **Chrysaki** via `Ctrl+K Ctrl+T`.\n\n### Windows Terminal\n\nAdd the contents of `windows-terminal/chrysaki.json` to the `\"schemes\": [...]` array in your `settings.json`, then set `\"colorScheme\": \"Chrysaki\"` in your profile defaults.\n\n### PowerShell\n\nDot-source the script in your `$PROFILE`:\n```powershell\n. \"path\\to\\chrysaki-psreadline.ps1\"\n```\n\n### Kitty\n\nSave `kitty/theme.conf` to `~/.config/kitty/theme.conf`, then add to `kitty.conf`:\n```conf\ninclude theme.conf\n```\n\n### tmux\n\nAppend `tmux/chrysaki.conf` to `~/.tmux.conf`, or source it:\n```bash\nsource-file ~/.tmux/chrysaki.conf\n```\n\n### Neovim\n\nCopy `nvim/chrysaki.lua` to `~/.config/nvim/colors/chrysaki.lua`, then:\n```lua\nvim.cmd(\"colorscheme chrysaki\")\n```\n\n### Gitui\n\nCopy `gitui/theme.ron` to `~/.config/gitui/theme.ron`. Gitui loads it automatically.\n\n### GTK\n\n```bash\nmkdir -p ~/.config/gtk-3.0 ~/.config/gtk-4.0\ncp gtk/gtk.css ~/.config/gtk-3.0/gtk.css\ncp gtk/gtk.css ~/.config/gtk-4.0/gtk.css\ncp gtk/settings.ini ~/.config/gtk-3.0/settings.ini\n```\n\nLog out and back in for changes to take effect.\n\n### Steam / SteamOS\n\nCopy `steam/libraryroot.custom.css` to the Steam UI directory:\n- Linux/SteamOS: `~/.steam/steam/steamui/libraryroot.custom.css`\n- Windows: `C:/Program Files (x86)/Steam/steamui/libraryroot.custom.css`\n\nRestart Steam.\n\n### Firefox\n\n1. Enable `toolkit.legacyUserProfileCustomizations.stylesheets` in `about:config`\n2. Copy `firefox/userChrome.css` and `firefox/userContent.css` to `<profile>/chrome/`\n3. Restart Firefox\n\n### Discord (Vencord)\n\nCopy `discord/Chrysaki.theme.css` to `~/.config/Vencord/themes/` and enable in Vencord settings.\n\n### Spotify (Spicetify)\n\n```bash\nmkdir -p ~/.config/spicetify/Themes/Chrysaki\ncp spicetify/* ~/.config/spicetify/Themes/Chrysaki/\nspicetify config current_theme Chrysaki\nspicetify config color_scheme Base\nspicetify apply\n```\n\n### Marp\n\n```bash\nmarp --theme marp/chrysaki.css input.md\n```\n\nOr in VS Code with the Marp extension, add to `.vscode/settings.json`:\n```json\n{\n    \"markdown.marp.themes\": [\"./marp/chrysaki.css\"]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## CSS Custom Properties\n\nDrop these into any CSS project to use Chrysaki tokens:\n\n```css\n--chrysaki-abyss:        #0f1117;\n--chrysaki-base:         #161821;\n--chrysaki-surface:      #1c1f2b;\n--chrysaki-raised:       #252836;\n--chrysaki-elevated:     #2e3142;\n--chrysaki-border:       #363a4f;\n--chrysaki-emerald:      #14664e;\n--chrysaki-emerald-lt:   #1a8a6a;\n--chrysaki-emerald-dim:  #0e4a38;\n--chrysaki-blue:         #122858;\n--chrysaki-blue-lt:      #1c3d7a;\n--chrysaki-blue-dim:     #0c1a40;\n--chrysaki-amethyst:     #3a2068;\n--chrysaki-amethyst-lt:  #583090;\n--chrysaki-amethyst-dim: #1e1040;\n--chrysaki-teal:         #197278;\n--chrysaki-teal-lt:      #20969c;\n--chrysaki-teal-dim:     #0f4f54;\n--chrysaki-blonde:       #FBB13C;\n--chrysaki-blonde-lt:    #FCC96A;\n--chrysaki-blonde-dim:   #C4861C;\n--chrysaki-error:        #8C2F39;\n--chrysaki-error-lt:     #b53f4a;\n--chrysaki-error-dim:    #5e1f25;\n--chrysaki-text:         #e0e2ea;\n--chrysaki-text-sec:     #a0a4b8;\n--chrysaki-text-muted:   #6a6e82;\n--chrysaki-text-inverse: #0f1117;\n```\n\n---\n\n*Part of the [obKidian](https://github.com/Kiriketsuki/obKidian) vault system.*\n","numLines":235,"startLine":1,"totalLines":235}}}
