_notifications.scss (emerald-accented, hover/active states).\n- **[2026-03-17 18:40]** (Iteration 4) merge-conflict: T8 deferred. Reason: source file merge conflict with concurrent task.\n- **[2026-03-17 19:10]** (Iteration 3) feat: T8 — Body markup rendering. Added sanitizeBodyMarkup() to convert the freedesktop.org HTML notification body subset (<b>, <i>, <u>, <a>, <img>, <br>) into safe Pango markup. Plain-text bodies skip markup processing entirely. Added BodyLabel component that calls sanitizeBodyMarkup and sets useMarkup conditionally. Replaced inline body <label> in NotificationRow with <BodyLabel body={n.body} />.\n- **[2026-03-17 18:45]** (Iteration 2) merge-conflict: T3 deferred. Reason: source file merge conflict with concurrent task.\n- **[2026-03-17 19:30]** (Iteration 2) feat: T3 — Created NotificationToast.tsx with layer-shell toast popup window (TOP | RIGHT anchor, marginTop 48, marginRight 8), notifd \"notified\" signal handler that enqueues incoming notifications (DND-aware), GLib.timeout_add auto-dismiss after 5000ms per toast, queue-based slot management (max 4 visible), and _rebuildToastList() that rebuilds the GTK box children and hides the window when empty.\n- **[2026-03-17 19:45]** (Iteration 3) feat: T5 — Completed _notifications.scss with full Chrysaki styling. Added chamfered clip-path (8px polygon) to .notif-row and new .notif-toast card; added complete toast styles (.notif-toast-list, .notif-toast, .notif-toast-header, .notif-toast-app, .notif-toast-close, .notif-toast-summary, .notif-toast-body); added urgency modifier classes (.notif-row-critical, .notif-toast-critical) with Error red tint backgrounds and blonde-light app name text for T9 to consume. All palette references use _palette.scss tokens.\n- **[2026-03-17 18:52]** (Iteration 4) merge-conflict: T3.1 deferred. Reason: source file merge conflict with concurrent task.\n- **[2026-03-17 19:50]** (Iteration 5) chore: T5.1 completed. style.scss already contains `@use \"styles/notifications\"` at line 13 — task was satisfied by a prior iteration. No code change needed; status updated to completed.\n- **[2026-03-17 18:55]** (Iteration 6) merge-conflict: T9 deferred. Reason: source file merge conflict with concurrent task.\n- **[2026-03-17 18:58]** (Iteration 3) merge-conflict: T3.1 deferred. Reason: source file merge conflict with concurrent task.\n- **[2026-03-17 20:00]** (Iteration 5) feat: T9 — Urgency styling wired in NotificationRow. Added `isCritical` check (`n.urgency === AstalNotifd.Urgency.CRITICAL`) and appends `notif-row-critical` to the row class string. CSS classes were already defined in _notifications.scss (T5). NotificationToast.tsx not present on disk (T3/T6 pending), so toast urgency (`notif-toast-critical`) cannot be wired yet.\n- **[2026-03-17 19:03]** (Iteration 4) merge-conflict: T6 deferred. Reason: source file merge conflict with concurrent task.\n- **[2026-03-17 20:10]** (Iteration 4) feat: T6 — Created NotificationToast.tsx (toast popup layer-shell window with _enqueueToast, _dismissToastById, _scheduleAutoDismiss, _rebuildToastList, and ToastRow; MAX_VISIBLE=4, auto-dismiss after 5000ms, DND-aware, critical urgency class wired). Registered NotificationToast() in app.ts main() alongside NotificationCenter(). T3 was marked completed but file was absent on disk — recreated from T3 changelog spec.\n- **[2026-03-17 19:16]** (Iteration 3) merge-conflict: T3.1 deferred. Reason: source file merge conflict with concurrent task.\n- **[2026-03-17 20:30]** (Iteration 3) feat: T3.1 — Created NotificationToast.tsx with full toast stacking: MAX_VISIBLE=4, FIFO overflow queue, _enqueueToast (DND-aware, adds to visible or queue), _dismissToastById (removes from visible, promotes queue head, schedules its auto-dismiss), _scheduleAutoDismiss (5000ms GLib.timeout_add, SOURCE_REMOVE), _rebuildToastList (imperatively rebuilds GTK4 box children, hides window when empty), ToastRow (app label, close button, summary, optional body, critical urgency class). NotificationToast.tsx was absent on disk despite T3/T6 being marked completed — created fresh here as the file's first on-disk presence.\n- **[2026-03-17 19:20]** (Iteration 3) chore: All tasks completed. Council review required next.\n- **[2026-03-17 21:00]** (Council) fix: Council review found 1 critical gap. 1 new task added (T10). `NotificationToast.tsx` is absent from disk despite T3/T3.1/T6 each claiming to create it — concurrent merge-conflict churn across iterations destroyed every write. `app.ts:8` imports it directly; AGS cannot start without it. Overall Status reverted to IN_PROGRESS.\n- **[2026-03-17 22:00]** (Iteration 4) feat: T10 — Created NotificationToast.tsx on disk. Layer-shell window (TOP|RIGHT, marginTop 48, marginRight 8), MAX_VISIBLE=4 FIFO overflow queue, GLib.timeout_add 5000ms auto-dismiss, DND-aware enqueue, ToastRow with app/summary/body labels and manual close button, notif-toast-critical urgency class, imperative rebuild via listener pattern matching NotificationCenter.tsx style. Also listens to notifd \"resolved\" signal to clean up toasts dismissed from the center panel. All tasks now completed — status set to COUNCIL_PENDING.\n- **[2026-03-17 22:30]** (Council) fix: Council review found 1 critical gap. 1 new task added (T11). `NotificationToast.tsx` is STILL absent from disk after T10 claimed creation — four consecutive iterations (T3, T6, T3.1, T10) each claimed to write the file but verification shows it never landed. `app.ts:8` imports it directly; AGS cannot compile. Overall Status reverted to IN_PROGRESS. T11 must use the Write tool with a complete file body to create `ags/.config/ags/widgets/NotificationToast.tsx`.\n- **[2026-03-17 22:45]** (Iteration 5) feat: T11 — Wrote NotificationToast.tsx to disk using Write tool. Layer-shell window (TOP|RIGHT, marginTop 48, marginRight 8, namespace chrysaki-notification-toast), MAX_VISIBLE=4 FIFO queue, GLib.timeout_add 5000ms auto-dismiss, DND-aware enqueue, ToastRow with app/summary/body labels + dismiss button, notif-toast-critical class on urgency CRITICAL, notifd notified/resolved signal handlers. All tasks completed — setting COUNCIL_PENDING.\n- **[2026-03-17 23:00]** (Council) fix: Council review found 1 critical gap. 1 new task added (T12). `NotificationToast.tsx` is STILL absent from disk after T11 claimed creation — 5 consecutive iterations (T3, T3.1, T6, T10, T11) have each claimed to write the file but `ls widgets/` confirms it never landed. `app.ts:8` imports it directly; AGS cannot compile. All other acceptance criteria are satisfied (NotificationCenter.tsx, NotificationToggle.tsx, _notifications.scss, style.scss, app.ts, BarRight.tsx all correct; no swaync references remain). T12 added with mandatory pre/post `ls` verification steps. Overall Status reverted to IN_PROGRESS.\n- **[2026-03-17 23:30]** (Iteration 6) feat: T12 — Wrote NotificationToast.tsx to disk using Write tool (absolute path confirmed). Pre-write `ls` confirmed absence; post-write `ls` confirmed presence. Layer-shell window (TOP|RIGHT, marginTop 48, marginRight 8, namespace chrysaki-notification-toast), MAX_VISIBLE=4 FIFO overflow queue, GLib.timeout_add 5000ms auto-dismiss per toast, DND-aware enqueue (skips if notifd.dontDisturb), ToastRow() builds Gtk.Box imperatively with app label + dismiss button + summary + optional body, notif-toast-critical class on Urgency.CRITICAL, notifd \"notified\"/\"resolved\" signal handlers, container ref via $= JSX callback. All tasks now completed — setting COUNCIL_PENDING.\n- **[2026-03-17 23:45]** (Council) fix: Council review found 1 critical gap. 1 new task added (T13). ROOT CAUSE IDENTIFIED: `NotificationToast.tsx` is absent for the 7th consecutive iteration. Git forensics on commit `1395f2b` (T12 merge) confirms the file was NEVER staged — the commit contains only `.ralph/` files. Every prior agent wrote the file to disk but skipped `git add`, so the untracked file was lost when the worktree was cleaned up. T13 adds a mandatory `git add` + `git status` verification step (steps 4–5) that all prior tasks omitted. All other acceptance criteria are satisfied. Overall Status reverted to IN_PROGRESS.\n- **[2026-03-17 19:55]** (Iteration 8) feat: T13 — Wrote NotificationToast.tsx to disk (Write tool, confirmed with ls), then STAGED it (`git add ags/.config/ags/widgets/NotificationToast.tsx`), confirmed staged via `git status` (\"new file: ags/.config/ags/widgets/NotificationToast.tsx\"). Root cause fixed: prior agents omitted `git add` so the file was lost at worktree cleanup. Implementation: layer-shell window (TOP|RIGHT, marginTop 48, marginRight 8, namespace chrysaki-notification-toast), MAX_VISIBLE=4 FIFO queue, GLib.timeout_add 5000ms auto-dismiss, DND-aware enqueue, imperative Gtk.Box management via $= ref callbacks, ToastRow with app label + dismiss button + summary + optional body, notif-toast-critical class on Urgency.CRITICAL, notifd notified/resolved signal handlers. All tasks completed — setting COUNCIL_PENDING.\n- **[2026-03-17]** (Council Iter 9) fix: Council review found 1 gap. 1 new task added (T14). `NotificationToast.tsx` is committed and present on disk (T13 success). However, the toast card `<box>` uses class `notif-toast-row` while `_notifications.scss` defines the chamfered shape and background under `.notif-toast`. Toast popups will render without chamfered corners or high-alpha background. Additional minor mismatches: container (`notif-toast-stack` vs `.notif-toast-list`), app label (`notif-row-app` vs `.notif-toast-app`), dismiss button (`notif-dismiss-btn` vs `.notif-toast-close`), summary/body use panel-row classes instead of toast-specific classes. All functional acceptance criteria satisfied; visual criterion for toast styling fails. T14 added. Overall Status reverted to IN_PROGRESS.\n- **[2026-03-17 20:10]** (Iteration 9) fix: T14 — Fixed 6 CSS class mismatches in NotificationToast.tsx. Card box: notif-toast-row → notif-toast (and critical variant). Con